Consider the inheritance hierarchy: class Animal {} class Dog extends Animal {}. What is the output of the following code?
```java
var animal = new Dog();
System.out.println(animal.getClass().getSimpleName());
```

Given the classes:
```java
class Base { void run() { System.out.println("Base"); } }
class Derived extends Base { void run() { System.out.println("Derived"); } }
```
What is the result of executing this code?
```java
Base obj = new Derived();
var newObj = obj;
newObj.run();
```
